## 5. Critical Observations & Vulnerabilities

| #   | File/Module                                                 | Category       | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           | Remediation                                                                                                                                                                                                          |
| --- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1   | `apps/api/src/middleware/security.ts:4-20`                  | 🔴 Security    | Regex patterns with `g` flag cause `.test()` to alternate results due to `lastIndex` state persistence. A payload matching a pattern on first call may not match on second call from a different request.                                             | Remove `g` flag from all regex literals in `DANGEROUS_PATTERNS` and `SQL_INJECTION_PATTERNS`, or clone regex per invocation via `new RegExp(pattern.source, "i")`                                                    |
| 2   | `apps/worker/src/main.ts:210-214`                           | 🔴 Data Loss   | Failed tasks are deleted from SQS before the DLQ can receive them. `deleteMessage()` is called in the same promise chain as `processMessage()`, so any failure (exception or returned `{ ok: false }`) results in message deletion with no retry.     | Split the chain: only call `deleteMessage` when `result.ok === true`. Failed messages will return to the queue via visibility timeout and eventually hit the DLQ after `maxReceiveCount: 3`                          |
| 3   | `infra/terraform/compute.tf:101,119`                        | 🟡 Security    | ECR repositories have `image_tag_mutability = "MUTABLE"`, allowing tags (including `:latest`) to be overwritten. An attacker with push access can replace a known-good image with a compromised one.                                                  | Set `image_tag_mutability = "IMMUTABLE"` on both ECR repos. Use unique tags (git SHA) for deployments instead of `:latest`                                                                                           |
| 4   | `apps/api/src/app.ts:52-59`                                 | 🟡 Performance | Global IP rate limiter at 100 req/15min (~1 request per 9 seconds) is extremely restrictive. The per-user limiter after auth adds additional throttling. This will cause failures for legitimate multi-tab users and dashboards that batch-load data. | Increase to at least 300-500 per 15min, or move the global limiter to only cover public/unauthenticated routes. The per-user limiter provides fine-grained control for auth routes                                   |
| 5   | `apps/api/src/app.ts:48`                                    | 🟡 Performance | `express.json({ limit: "1mb" })` — Body parser rejects anything over 1MB. Document uploads with base64-encoded payloads or large form submissions will hit this limit silently.                                                                       | Increase to `10mb` to match the Next.js server action limit (`bodySizeLimit: "25mb"` in next.config.mjs). Document uploads use multipart (multer) so aren't affected, but form submissions with attachments could be |
